The Special Investigating Unit (SIU) says it is yet to investigate the whereabouts of the outstanding money and assets linked to the Digital Vibes saga. The SIU has said it had been granted an order to freeze R22 million held in bank and investment accounts linked to the media company. The SIU says it will also approach the Special Tribunal, where the order was granted, to have the R150-million COVID-19 media campaign contract – that was irregularly awarded by the Health Department to Digital Vibes – declared unlawful and invalid. SIU spokesperson, Kaizer Kganyago elaborates: 